.SH NAME
HTMLDetailsElement.toggle_event \- HTMLDetailsElement: toggle event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]toggle\f[B]\f[R] event fires when the
\f[CR]open\f[R]/\f[CR]closed\f[R] state of a \f[CR]<details>\f[R]
element is toggled.
.PP
This event is not cancelable and does not bubble.
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] The \f[CR]toggle\f[R] event is also available in a
different form on \f[CR]HTMLElement\f[R]; this version fires on popover
elements just after they are shown or hidden.
See the \f[CR]HTMLElement\f[R] \f[CR]toggle event\f[R] page for more
information.
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\[dq]toggle\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {});

ontoggle = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {};
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A generic \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EXAMPLES
This example logs chapters that are open.
Chapters are removed from the log when they are closed.
